    <item>
      <title>Board Game Cup</title>
      <link>https://blog.jverkamp.com/maker/3d-printing/2020-12-30-board-game-cup/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 30 Dec 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://blog.jverkamp.com/maker/3d-printing/2020-12-30-board-game-cup/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I play &amp;hellip; a lot of board games. This year has been hard to do that in person&lt;sup id=&#34;fnref:1&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:1&#34; class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; role=&#34;doc-noteref&#34;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;, but I still get a chance from time to time. Most recently, I played &lt;a href=&#34;https://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/270970/century-new-world&#34;&gt;Century: A New World&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;sup id=&#34;fnref:2&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:2&#34; class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; role=&#34;doc-noteref&#34;&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One component I really love that came with that game was a set of four small plastic bowls that hold the various goods (colored wooden cubes). It&amp;rsquo;s&amp;hellip; kind of brilliant. There are a few other games that could use something like that (&lt;em&gt;cough cough&lt;/em&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/110327/lords-waterdeep&#34;&gt;Lords of Waterdeep&lt;/a&gt;)&amp;hellip; and I have a 3D printer. Let&amp;rsquo;s make some!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure&gt;
    &lt;img src=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/maker/board-game-cup/final-cup.jpg&#34;/&gt; 
&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Links:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/maker/board-game-cup/board-game-cup.FCStd&#34;&gt;FreeCAD file&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/maker/board-game-cup/board-game-cup-small.stl&#34;&gt;Small cup STL&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/maker/board-game-cup/board-game-cup-small.stl&#34;&gt;Larger cup (pictured above) STL&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>3D COVID-19 Ornament</title>
      <link>https://blog.jverkamp.com/maker/3d-printing/2020-12-24-3d-covid-ornament/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 24 Dec 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://blog.jverkamp.com/maker/3d-printing/2020-12-24-3d-covid-ornament/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;So. This was actually what I originally intended to make when I made the &lt;a href=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/maker/3d-printing/2020-12-22-2d-covid-ornament/&#34;&gt;2d ornaments&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure&gt;
    &lt;img src=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/maker/covid-ornaments/3d/tinkercad-final.png&#34;/&gt; 
&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Full 3D coronavirus!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, what I kept getting was something more like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure&gt;
    &lt;img src=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/maker/covid-ornaments/3d/covid-failure.jpg&#34;/&gt; 
&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No matter how I tweaked the support settings, I could not get the little knobs to print. I even tried printing it in halves, but only half of it came out still. So it goes. Perhaps next year. &lt;sup id=&#34;fnref:1&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:1&#34; class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; role=&#34;doc-noteref&#34;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; Eesh that&amp;rsquo;s a terrible picture too.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Links:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/maker/covid-ornaments/3d/covid-3d.stl&#34;&gt;Original STL model&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4166787&#34;&gt;original source&lt;/a&gt;, licensed under CC BY-NC)&lt;sup id=&#34;fnref:2&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:2&#34; class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; role=&#34;doc-noteref&#34;&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/maker/covid-ornaments/3d/covid-3d-with-hanger.stl&#34;&gt;With hangler&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/maker/covid-ornaments/3d/covid-3d-with-hanger-and-year.stl&#34;&gt;With hanger and year&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/maker/covid-ornaments/3d/covid-ornament.f3d&#34;&gt;Fusion 360 file&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.tinkercad.com/things/lytsxfSYEEd-stunning-bigery-albar&#34;&gt;Tinkercad file&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
